sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    
    actor Client
    participant Gateway as ApiGatewayController
    participant Controller as AuthController
    participant Service as AuthService
    participant Security as AuthenticationManager
    participant JWT as JwtService
    participant Filter as JwtAuthenticationFilter
    participant DB as UserRepository (DB)

    %% Registration Flow
    rect rgb(245, 245, 250)
    note right of Client: 1. User Registration Flow
    Client->>Gateway: POST /gateway/api/auth/register (username, password, etc.)
    Gateway->>Controller: Proxy to /api/auth/register
    Controller->>Service: register(RegisterRequest)
    Service->>DB: Check if username/email exists
    alt User already exists
        DB-->>Service: Existing record found
        Service-->>Controller: throw IllegalArgumentException
        Controller-->>Gateway: 400 Bad Request
        Gateway-->>Client: 400 Bad Request (Error)
    else New user
        DB-->>Service: No existing record
        Service->>DB: Save encoded password & user details
        DB-->>Service: Valid User Entity
        Service-->>Controller: LoginResponse DTO
        Controller-->>Gateway: 201 Created (with Tokens)
        Gateway-->>Client: 201 Created (with Tokens)
    end
    end

    %% Login Flow
    rect rgb(240, 250, 240)
    note right of Client: 2. Main Login Flow (OAuth 2.0 Upgraded)
    Client->>Gateway: POST /gateway/api/auth/login (username, password)
    Gateway->>Controller: Proxy to /api/auth/login
    Controller->>Service: login(LoginRequest)
    Service->>Security: authenticate(UsernamePasswordAuthenticationToken)
    Security->>DB: Load UserDetails by Username
    DB-->>Security: User details + hashed password
    Security-->>Service: Valid Authentication Context
    
    Service->>JWT: generateAccessToken(Id, Username, Roles)
    JWT-->>Service: Returns JWT Access Token
    Service->>JWT: generateRefreshToken(Id)
    JWT-->>Service: Returns JWT Refresh Token
    
    Service-->>Controller: LoginResponse DTO
    Note right of Controller: Formatted to RFC 6749:<br>access_token, refresh_token, token_type, expires_in, scope
    Controller-->>Gateway: 200 OK (LoginResponse)
    Gateway-->>Client: 200 OK (OAuth 2.0 JSON Payload)
    end

    %% Refresh Token Flow
    rect rgb(250, 240, 230)
    note right of Client: 3. Token Refresh Flow
    Client->>Gateway: POST /gateway/api/auth/refresh (refresh_token payload)
    Gateway->>Controller: Proxy to /api/auth/refresh
    Controller->>Service: refreshToken(RefreshTokenRequest)
    Service->>JWT: validateToken(refresh_token)
    alt Invalid/Expired Token
        JWT-->>Service: InvalidTokenException
        Service-->>Controller: throws IllegalArgumentException
        Controller-->>Gateway: 401 Unauthorized
        Gateway-->>Client: 401 Unauthorized
    else Valid Token
        JWT-->>Service: Validity Confirmed (claims/sub extracted)
        Service->>JWT: generateAccessToken(...)
        JWT-->>Service: New JWT Access Token
        Service->>JWT: generateRefreshToken(...)
        JWT-->>Service: New JWT Refresh Token
        Service-->>Controller: LoginResponse DTO
        Controller-->>Gateway: 200 OK (New LoginResponse)
        Gateway-->>Client: 200 OK (Rotated access & refresh tokens)
    end
    end

    %% Protected Resource Access Flow (e.g. Agents)
    rect rgb(250, 240, 250)
    note right of Client: 4. Secure Resource Access
    Client->>Gateway: POST /api/agents (Header: "Authorization: Bearer <access_token>")
    Gateway->>Filter: Routes request, Filter intercepts
    Note over Gateway,Filter: JwtAuthenticationFilter runs before Controller
    Filter->>JWT: Validate token signature & expiry
    JWT-->>Filter: Token valid, extract Claims
    Filter->>Filter: Set SecurityContextHolder
    Filter->>Controller: Forward request to target Controller
    Controller-->>Gateway: 201 Created
    Gateway-->>Client: 201 Created (Authorized Request processed)
    end